  "description": "<h2>Body Parts of Man with Name: Understanding the Human Anatomy</h2>\n<p><strong>Body parts of man with name</strong> is a phrase that opens up a fascinating exploration into the intricate design of the human body. Whether you’re a student, a fitness enthusiast, or just curious about anatomy, knowing the names and functions of various body parts can enhance your understanding of how we move, feel, and live. In this article, we will take a detailed journey through the primary body parts of a man, highlighting their names and explaining their roles in everyday life. Along the way, we’ll also touch on related terms that help paint a fuller picture of human anatomy.</p>\n<h2>The Head and Facial Features</h2>\n<p>The head is the control center of the body, housing the brain, which governs everything from thought to movement. When we talk about the body parts of man with name related to the head, several key areas come to mind.</p>\n<h3>Skull and Scalp</h3>\n<p>The skull is the bony structure that protects the brain. It is divided into the cranium (which encloses the brain) and the facial bones. Covering the skull is the scalp, a layer of skin and hair follicles that protect the head and keep it warm.</p>\n<h3>Face: Eyes, Nose, Mouth, and Ears</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Eyes:</strong> The organs of vision, responsible for sight and perception of light.</li>\n<li><strong>Nose:</strong> The center for smell and also an airway for breathing.</li>\n<li><strong>Mouth:</strong> Contains the lips, teeth, tongue, and palate; essential for eating, speaking, and breathing.</li>\n<li><strong>Ears:</strong> Organs of hearing and balance.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Each of these facial features plays a vital role in communication and sensory experience.</p>\n<h2>The Neck and Torso</h2>\n<p>Moving downward from the head, the neck connects the head to the torso and supports vital structures such as the trachea and esophagus.</p>\n<h3>The Neck: Support and Mobility</h3>\n<p>The neck